conspicuous /kənˈspɪkjʊəs/

1. ADJ If someone or something is conspicuous , people can see or notice them very easily. 显眼的 

例： Most people don't want to be too conspicuous. 大多数人不愿过于显眼。 

2. conspicuously ADV 显眼地 

例： Britain continues to follow U.S. policy in this and other areas where American policies have most conspicuously failed. 英国在这个以及其他领域继续跟随美国已经明显失败了的政策。

